.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F52652e63365208885f555c81484ff15eb2155f66-1447x859.jpg&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="Bar Design NYC, Bolt, Bolt Builds, Bolt Builds NYC, Bolt Builds New York City, Bolt Design NYC, Bolt New York City, Boutique Design Agency New York, Custom Interior Design New York, Custom millwork NYC, Elegant Hospitality Interiors NYC, High-End Bar Design NYC, High-End Interior Design Agency NYC, High-End Retail Design New York, High-end Millwork NYC, Hospitality, Hospitality Interior Design New York, Innovative Hospitality Solutions New York, Luxery Millwork NYC, Luxury Bar Design NYC, Luxury Hospitality Consultants NYC, Luxury Millwork NYC, NYC Residential Interior Designers, New York, New York City, New York Design and Branding for Hospitality, New York Hospitality Branding, New York Retail Interior Design, Sophisticated Branding Agency NYC, luxury Hospitality Design NYC" width="1447" height="859" class="absolute object-cover w-full h-full z-0 inset-0" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 300vw, (max-width: 1000px) 200vw, 100vw"/></div><div class="border-x flex-1 flex flex-col justify-end"></div></header><div class="z-20 relative bg-white"><div class="sticky top-0 invisible"><div class="px-unit absolute left-0 right-0 bg-white"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-b"></div></div></div><div class="px-unit"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-x"><div class="sticky top-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-2 pb-4"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3 pr-2"><p class="text-current font-body text-3xl">Site Super </p></div><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-2"><h3 class="text-current font-body text-md">February 4, 2026</h3></div></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-8 pb-unit"><div class="col-start-1 col-end-13 md:col-start-2 md:col-end-12 lg:col-start-4 lg:col-end-12 xl:col-start-4 xl:col-end-10"><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>About Bolt</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Bolt is a full-service <strong>Design + Build</strong> firm and fully insured <strong>General Contractor</strong> based in Brooklyn. We specialize in design-forward hospitality, retail, and residential projects that merge classical sensibility with innovative construction and fabrication methods. We believe that great design is only as strong as its execution — and that means being just as rigorous about budgets, schedules, and communication as we are about creative vision.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>The Role</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Bolt is seeking an experienced <strong>Construction Site Superintendent</strong> to oversee day-to-day field operations on <strong>New York City–based</strong> hospitality, retail, and residential projects. This is a hands-on, site-first role for someone who knows how to run a clean, safe, well-coordinated job site and take pride in the details.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">As Site Super, you’ll be Bolt’s on-site lead — responsible for sequencing work, coordinating trades, maintaining quality and safety standards, and ensuring projects move forward efficiently. You’ll work closely with Bolt’s Project Managers, designers, subcontractors, and inspectors to deliver high-quality builds in a demanding NYC environment.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Manage <strong>daily on-site construction activities</strong>, including trade coordination, sequencing, and site logistics</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Maintain and update <strong>short- and long-term look-ahead schedules</strong> in coordination with the Project Manager</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Supervise subcontractors to ensure work is executed safely, efficiently, and in accordance with drawings and specifications</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Enforce <strong>NYC jobsite safety standards</strong>, including OSHA compliance and site-specific safety plans</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Coordinate and attend <strong>DOB, FDNY, and special inspections</strong>, ensuring readiness and compliance</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Perform daily site walks to verify quality, progress, and cleanliness</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Review drawings and details in the field and flag constructability issues or conflicts early</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Track deliveries, material storage, and site access logistics in dense urban conditions</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Maintain clear daily reports, progress photos, and punch lists</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Serve as Bolt’s on-site representative with inspectors, subcontractors, landlords, and building management</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Support punch, closeout, and turnover processes to ensure smooth project completion</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>5–10+ years of experience</strong> as a Site Superintendent or Lead Foreman on <strong>NYC construction projects</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Strong background in <strong>interior build-outs</strong>, hospitality, retail, or high-end commercial work</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Deep understanding of <strong>NYC construction logistics</strong>, including occupied buildings, tight sites, and accelerated schedules</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Working knowledge of <strong>NYC DOB, FDNY, inspections, and code requirements</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Ability to read and interpret architectural, structural, and MEP drawings</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Proven ability to coordinate multiple trades and keep work moving without sacrificing quality</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Strong leadership presence on site — calm, organized, and accountable</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Clear communicator who works well with Project Managers, designers, and subcontractors</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Pride in maintaining a clean, professional, and well-run job site</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Reliable, proactive, and solutions-oriented mindset</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Why Bolt</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>See your work built — and built fast.</strong> At Bolt, you won’t be stuck pushing paper for years before seeing results. Our projects move quickly, and the work you put in becomes something real, tangible, and lasting.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Be hands-on.</strong> You won’t be siloed behind a screen — you’ll be in the field, in meetings, on walk-throughs, and fully involved in the process from start to finish.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Work in the heart of Greenpoint.</strong> Our studio is based in one of Brooklyn’s most creative neighborhoods — surrounded by great food, inspiring spaces, and a thriving design community.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Join a company on the rise.</strong> Bolt is entering a new chapter of growth — and we’re building something special. You’ll help shape the future of the company, not just execute the present.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Build projects you’re proud of.</strong> From thoughtful restaurants to bold retail environments, you’ll be part of a team that sweats the details and cares deeply about design, craft, and execution.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Work with good people.</strong> We’re a tight-knit, driven team that takes pride in what we do — and has fun doing it. We value trust, accountability, and creative problem-solving.</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Compensation</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">This is a <strong>full-time, in-person, field-based role</strong> on active construction sites across <strong>New York City</strong>.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">The base hourly pay range for this position is <strong>$28.00 to $36.00</strong> depending on experience and qualifications. Bolt also offers performance-based bonus opportunities, consistent project pipeline, and long-term growth potential within a design-forward construction firm.</p><div class="mt-16 pb-12"><div class="px-6 py-8 bg-faint text-center"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">To apply for this job, please email your resume to<!-- --> <a href="mailto:hello@bolt.build" class="font-bold hover:text-blue transition-colors border-b border-current border-dotted">hello@bolt.build ↗</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><footer class="bg-white pb-unit px-unit relative z-[1000]"><div class="bg-white border border-b border-black pt-unit pb-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3"><a class="text-current hover:text-yellow transition-colors" href="../index.html"><div class="w-[24px]"><div class="w-full "><svg width="100%" height="100%" viewBox="0 0 114 265" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><title>Bolt Design NYC Logo</title><path d="M38 0H0.5V208H76.5V265H114V56.5H38V0Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></div></div></a></div><div class="col-start-7 col-end-13 lg:col-start-5 lg:co